  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries and is typically covered under specific criminal legislation. It is considered a serious financial crime that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money to make it appear legitimate. Laws against money laundering are designed to prevent criminals from profiting from illegal activities and to disrupt organized crime. Many countries have comprehensive anti-money laundering (AML) laws that impose criminal penalties, including fines and imprisonment, for those found guilty of such activities.",
